 The results point to/show that farmers' education 
 (Enuc) and farm size (LNFSIZE) had a positive and 
 highly significant effect on the amount of extension contact. These results are agreeing with/matching up with/working regularly with the 
 F &amp;S findings for the Indian Punjab that larger 
 and more educated farmers have better access to 
 improved information (e.g., extension). T &amp; V extension also had a positive and (meaningful numbers) effect on the amount of extension contact. 
 More regular visits and greater extension contacts 
 have also been reported under the T &amp; V system 
 in Sri Skinnya (Samarsingh et al., 1988). Other 
 (numbers that change/things that change) such as ROAD had the expected positive 
 effect on the chance of extension contact, but 
 the effects were not significant. 
 3.2. Knowledge of recommended technology 
 
 Increased extension contact may not be very 
 useful unless it improves farmers' knowledge of 
 new technology leading to higher working well. 
 Table 1 shows Tobit moving backward results for factors 
 affecting farmers' knowledge as measured by a 
 score of farmers' correct answers to a series of 
 questions on improved wheat technology (KNowscaR). A total of six knowledge (numbers that change/things that change) were 
 linearly grouped to form the knowledge score 
 (number or thing that changes). These included farmer's knowledge of 
 (1) names of new wheat varieties, (2) recommended doses of (material that makes plants grow better)s, (3) (material that makes plants grow better) nutrient 
 composition, (4) (material that makes plants grow better) nutrient carry-over effects, (5) herbicide names and doses and (6) the 
 appropriate herbicides for different weed species. 
 Weights of 1 and 0 were given to correct and 
 wrong answers to these six questions, (match up each pair of items in order), and KNowscoR is then the total score with 
 a possible range from 0 (wrong answers to all 
 questions) to 6 (correct answers for all questions). 
 Model 1 measures possible overall effects of 
 T &amp; V and Model 2 measures the effect of both 
 amount as well as quality of extension guidance for 
 4 We have specified log changes of the continuous 
 (numbers that change/things that change) (e.g., FSIZE and AGE) in order to avoid the heteroscedasticity problem usually watched/followed in linear models 
 (Maddala, 1983). 
 
 those farmers who have contact with extension. 
 T &amp; V extension appeared to have no effect on 
 farmers' knowledge of new technology for farmers as a whole in T &amp; V districts (column 1 of 
 Table 1). On the other hand, those farmers with 
 extension contact (ExT) had a much higher 
 knowledge score, even after allowing for their 
 better educational status (Model 2). The interaction of T &amp; V with extension contact was (related to numbers) non-significant and negative, suggesting no 
 effect of T &amp; V on quality of extension guidance. 
 Other (numbers that change/things that change) which have positive and (related to numbers) highly significant effects on farmers' knowledge score are Enuc (level of formal education) 
 and RADIO (farmer listens to an extension-oriented radio program). 5 
 We also sub-divided the (number or thing that changes) for knowledge score, KNowscoR, into two parts/pieces: 
 knowledge of recommendations (KNOWREc) and 
 general technical knowledge (KNOWTECH). The 
 KNOWREC (number or thing that changes) represents the possible influence of extension in a communications role (e.g., 
 whether the farmer knows the (material that makes plants grow better) dose recommended by the extension system), while the 
 KNOWTECH (number or thing that changes) represents the effects of extension in an educational role (i.e., whether the 
 farmer understands the nutrient_ composition of 
 different commercial (material that makes plants grow better) products or the 
 possible carry-over effects of different (material that makes plants grow better) 
 (vitamins, minerals, protein, etc.) from one season to the next). In both 
 cases, the KNOWREC and KNOWTECH (numbers that change/things that change) have 
 a possible value range from 0 to 3. 6 It was 
 guessed that T &amp; V extension has focused on extension in a communications rather than 
 educational role (Byerlee, 1987). In fact, extension contact in Model 2 showed a positive and 
 
